WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:30.447 --> 00:00:31.948 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
When I was little,

00:00:32.032 --> 00:00:36.745 position:50% align:center
I went on the town camping trip
where I met an interesting boy.

00:00:38.747 --> 00:00:40.457 position:50% align:center
--[MIRA] Hey!
--[AO gasps]

00:00:42.417 --> 00:00:45.170 position:50% align:center
What are you doing way
out here all by yourself?

00:00:45.253 --> 00:00:46.838 position:50% align:center
[AO]
What am I doing?

00:00:46.921 --> 00:00:49.507 position:50% align:center
Trying not to be mad.

00:00:49.591 --> 00:00:51.217 position:50% align:center
Wow!

00:00:59.642 --> 00:01:02.604 position:50% align:center
All the light from
the campsite interferes.

00:01:02.687 --> 00:01:04.022 position:50% align:center
Look, there's Jupiter.

00:01:05.106 --> 00:01:07.025 position:50% align:center
Which one?

00:01:07.108 --> 00:01:08.401 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Here.

00:01:08.485 --> 00:01:10.153 position:50% align:center
Oh, thank you!

00:01:10.236 --> 00:01:11.738 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Look, right up there.

00:01:14.324 --> 00:01:15.909 position:50% align:center
Oh! That dot?

00:01:15.992 --> 00:01:19.204 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Dot? Uh, yeah.

00:01:19.287 --> 00:01:21.331 position:50% align:center
You can't see it
with binoculars,

00:01:21.414 --> 00:01:23.833 position:50% align:center
but Jupiter has stripes
and thin rings circling it.

00:01:23.917 --> 00:01:25.001 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Whoa...

00:01:25.085 --> 00:01:27.504 position:50% align:center
Also, it has about
70 moons in its orbit.

00:01:27.587 --> 00:01:29.172 position:50% align:center
Wow, you know a lot!

00:01:29.255 --> 00:01:32.175 position:50% align:center
So then, what's your name?

00:01:32.258 --> 00:01:33.218 position:50% align:center
I'm Ao.

00:01:33.301 --> 00:01:34.678 position:50% align:center
And my name's Mira!

00:01:34.761 --> 00:01:36.346 position:50% align:center
Ah! The star!

00:01:36.429 --> 00:01:37.764 position:50% align:center
I'm a star?

00:01:37.847 --> 00:01:39.849 position:50% align:center
Oh, that's not what I meant.

00:01:39.933 --> 00:01:41.476 position:50% align:center
The variable star, Mira.

00:01:41.559 --> 00:01:43.812 position:50% align:center
It's in the Cetus constellation,
and it's unusual because

00:01:43.895 --> 00:01:45.605 position:50% align:center
its brightness varies.

00:01:45.689 --> 00:01:46.815 position:50% align:center
How cool!

00:01:46.898 --> 00:01:49.234 position:50% align:center
I never knew I shared
a name with a star!

00:01:49.317 --> 00:01:52.529 position:50% align:center
What about you, Ao?
Is there a star with your name?

00:01:52.612 --> 00:01:55.156 position:50% align:center
No way. My name's
too weird for that.

00:01:55.240 --> 00:01:56.491 position:50% align:center
I don't think it's weird!

00:01:56.574 --> 00:01:57.701 position:50% align:center
Your name's cool!

00:01:57.784 --> 00:01:58.702 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:01:58.785 --> 00:01:59.953 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Besides...

00:02:00.036 --> 00:02:02.163 position:50% align:center
You could always just
name one after yourself!

00:02:02.247 --> 00:02:03.957 position:50% align:center
Name one?

00:02:04.040 --> 00:02:06.459 position:50% align:center
Nah, maybe an asteroid.

00:02:06.543 --> 00:02:09.254 position:50% align:center
If I discover an asteroid,
I'll get to name it.

00:02:09.337 --> 00:02:11.840 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Let's find one together, then!

00:02:11.923 --> 00:02:14.926 position:50% align:center
Let's do it! Find an asteroid!

00:02:15.010 --> 00:02:16.219 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:02:17.887 --> 00:02:21.683 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] After that night,
I never saw the boy again.

00:02:25.145 --> 00:02:27.230 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
And now, I'm in high school.

00:02:27.313 --> 00:02:29.190 position:50% align:center
I'm so excited to begin
the new school year

00:02:29.274 --> 00:02:30.442 position:50% align:center
with all of you.

00:02:30.525 --> 00:02:32.444 position:50% align:center
Especially those
who are just starting here.

00:02:32.527 --> 00:02:34.320 position:50% align:center
As we all work toward our goals,

00:02:34.404 --> 00:02:38.533 position:50% align:center
let's support each other and
help our peers do their best.

00:02:38.616 --> 00:02:41.202 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] As of today,
I'm a high schooler!

00:02:41.286 --> 00:02:43.288 position:50% align:center
And the one thing I've been
looking forward to most

00:02:43.371 --> 00:02:44.914 position:50% align:center
in high school is...

00:02:44.998 --> 00:02:47.250 position:50% align:center
...gone?!

00:02:47.334 --> 00:02:49.711 position:50% align:center
Huh? What's wrong,
Mira? You okay?

00:02:49.794 --> 00:02:52.005 position:50% align:center
Suzu! They've always
had an astronomy club,

00:02:52.088 --> 00:02:53.631 position:50% align:center
but now it's gone!

00:02:53.715 --> 00:02:56.176 position:50% align:center
I was so excited to join it
when I got into high school,

00:02:56.259 --> 00:02:58.762 position:50% align:center
but now my dreams
have all been crushed.

00:02:58.845 --> 00:02:59.763 position:50% align:center
Why?

00:02:59.846 --> 00:03:01.723 position:50% align:center
[ENDOU]
Yeah. About that...

00:03:01.806 --> 00:03:04.434 position:50% align:center
Oh, uh... Hi, Miss Endou.

00:03:04.517 --> 00:03:07.395 position:50% align:center
The Astronomy Club and
Geology Club have merged now.

00:03:07.479 --> 00:03:09.939 position:50% align:center
Why don't you join
the Earth Science Club?

00:03:10.023 --> 00:03:11.441 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
Earth Science...?

00:03:12.400 --> 00:03:14.110 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] I can't believe
the clubs have merged!

00:03:14.194 --> 00:03:16.071 position:50% align:center
Why would they do that?

00:03:16.154 --> 00:03:18.573 position:50% align:center
Maybe they just weren't
big enough on their own.

00:03:18.656 --> 00:03:20.408 position:50% align:center
Wait, that's not true!

00:03:20.492 --> 00:03:22.535 position:50% align:center
Remember last year's
cultural festival?

00:03:24.454 --> 00:03:27.916 position:50% align:center
Welcome to our sexy planetarium!

00:03:27.999 --> 00:03:30.043 position:50% align:center
It was an enormous success!

00:03:30.126 --> 00:03:32.504 position:50% align:center
Maybe that's got
something to do with it.

00:03:32.587 --> 00:03:34.172 position:50% align:center
They were
punished for that stunt.

00:03:34.255 --> 00:03:36.091 position:50% align:center
But that's not
the reason they merged.

00:03:36.174 --> 00:03:37.759 position:50% align:center
Punished, you say?

00:03:37.842 --> 00:03:39.344 position:50% align:center
[ENDOU]
They lost a few members,

00:03:39.427 --> 00:03:41.763 position:50% align:center
and there were some other issues
on the school's side of things.

00:03:41.846 --> 00:03:44.599 position:50% align:center
So, we decided merging
the clubs was the best option.

00:03:44.683 --> 00:03:46.935 position:50% align:center
and that's how we got
the Earth Sciences Club.

00:03:47.018 --> 00:03:48.395 position:50% align:center
Well...

00:03:48.478 --> 00:03:50.689 position:50% align:center
But looking up at the heavens
and down at the ground

00:03:50.772 --> 00:03:53.775 position:50% align:center
are literally opposites,
so how would that work?

00:03:53.858 --> 00:03:55.110 position:50% align:center
[SUZU]
I don't know.

00:03:55.193 --> 00:03:56.611 position:50% align:center
They're kind of the same
if you're looking at Earth

00:03:56.695 --> 00:03:58.321 position:50% align:center
from outer space.

00:03:58.405 --> 00:04:01.866 position:50% align:center
Good call! I really like
your galactic perspective!

00:04:01.950 --> 00:04:03.785 position:50% align:center
Stop. You're embarrassing me.

00:04:06.746 --> 00:04:10.291 position:50% align:center
So, uh, what galaxy
is the club room in?

00:04:10.375 --> 00:04:11.626 position:50% align:center
Very clever.

00:04:11.710 --> 00:04:14.254 position:50% align:center
The building is on
the far end of the campus.

00:04:17.048 --> 00:04:20.176 position:50% align:center
[SUZU] It's ancient. You think
it's still safe in there?

00:04:20.260 --> 00:04:21.636 position:50% align:center
[ENDOU]
Oh, stop.

00:04:21.720 --> 00:04:24.014 position:50% align:center
There are still of couple
drafty spots here and there,

00:04:24.097 --> 00:04:26.599 position:50% align:center
but we got all the leaks
repaired, at least.

00:04:26.683 --> 00:04:29.686 position:50% align:center
Hey. I brought
two prospective members!

00:04:33.940 --> 00:04:36.860 position:50% align:center
"Sky." "Earth." "Man"?

00:04:36.943 --> 00:04:38.194 position:50% align:center
Is it aliens?

00:04:38.278 --> 00:04:40.030 position:50% align:center
I don't think so?

00:04:41.322 --> 00:04:43.616 position:50% align:center
[MORINO]
Sorry. We're still adjusting.

00:04:43.700 --> 00:04:46.161 position:50% align:center
The club merger is
new to all of us, too.

00:04:46.244 --> 00:04:48.079 position:50% align:center
I'm the club president, Morino.

00:04:48.163 --> 00:04:49.831 position:50% align:center
From the Astronomy Club.

00:04:49.914 --> 00:04:52.083 position:50% align:center
And I'm vice president Sakurai.

00:04:52.167 --> 00:04:55.128 position:50% align:center
I used to be
in the Geology Club.

00:04:55.211 --> 00:04:57.464 position:50% align:center
Now choose!

00:04:57.547 --> 00:04:59.758 position:50% align:center
Sorry. Choose what?

00:04:59.841 --> 00:05:01.509 position:50% align:center
Geology or astronomy.

00:05:01.593 --> 00:05:03.303 position:50% align:center
Which one were
you hoping to join?

00:05:03.386 --> 00:05:04.679 position:50% align:center
If you're here for geology,

00:05:04.763 --> 00:05:06.931 position:50% align:center
you get this power stone set
that boosts your luck!

00:05:07.015 --> 00:05:08.892 position:50% align:center
It's for new members
only, though.

00:05:08.975 --> 00:05:10.185 position:50% align:center
--Now choose!
--[INOSE] Vice President!

00:05:10.268 --> 00:05:12.854 position:50% align:center
If you're too aggressive,
you'll scare her away!

00:05:12.937 --> 00:05:14.230 position:50% align:center
So sorry.

00:05:14.314 --> 00:05:16.858 position:50% align:center
Uh... She's really concerned
about the club ratio.

00:05:16.941 --> 00:05:19.694 position:50% align:center
Oh! I'm Inose, a second year.

00:05:19.778 --> 00:05:21.529 position:50% align:center
Geology.

00:05:21.613 --> 00:05:23.323 position:50% align:center
Manaka, a first year.

00:05:23.406 --> 00:05:25.033 position:50% align:center
I'm here for astronomy.

00:05:25.116 --> 00:05:27.285 position:50% align:center
I'm so glad that
there's another newbie!

00:05:27.369 --> 00:05:29.704 position:50% align:center
I was hoping for astronomy, too.

00:05:29.788 --> 00:05:31.915 position:50% align:center
So, um... You like stars?

00:05:31.998 --> 00:05:33.333 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Yeah!

00:05:33.416 --> 00:05:36.044 position:50% align:center
And there's something that
I've always wanted to do!

00:05:36.127 --> 00:05:39.255 position:50% align:center
You see... I wanna
discover an asteroid!

00:05:39.339 --> 00:05:40.507 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah?

00:05:40.590 --> 00:05:42.759 position:50% align:center
That's a pretty lofty goal
you've got there.

00:05:42.842 --> 00:05:45.345 position:50% align:center
Is that, like, a hard thing
to do or something?

00:05:45.428 --> 00:05:47.472 position:50% align:center
Some high schooler discovered
one in the past,

00:05:47.555 --> 00:05:49.224 position:50% align:center
but that was, like,
a world record.

00:05:49.307 --> 00:05:51.476 position:50% align:center
It's practically impossible,
to be honest.

00:05:51.559 --> 00:05:52.936 position:50% align:center
At least for our tiny club?

00:05:53.019 --> 00:05:54.229 position:50% align:center
[INOSE] You don't have to
crush her dreams like that,

00:05:54.312 --> 00:05:55.814 position:50% align:center
Vice President!

00:05:55.897 --> 00:05:57.315 position:50% align:center
Well...

00:05:57.399 --> 00:06:01.736 position:50% align:center
Maybe, but I made a promise
to a boy when I was little.

00:06:01.820 --> 00:06:04.322 position:50% align:center
What? Mira, why haven't
you told me about this?

00:06:04.406 --> 00:06:05.824 position:50% align:center
'Cause if I'd told you about it,

00:06:05.907 --> 00:06:08.201 position:50% align:center
you would never have
stopped grilling for more info.

00:06:08.284 --> 00:06:09.536 position:50% align:center
[SUZU]
Yeah! I'd string him up!

00:06:09.619 --> 00:06:10.912 position:50% align:center
Tell me his name!

00:06:10.995 --> 00:06:14.791 position:50% align:center
Ao. We promised we
would discover it together.

00:06:14.874 --> 00:06:16.626 position:50% align:center
He told me that he wanted
to have an asteroid

00:06:16.710 --> 00:06:18.336 position:50% align:center
named after him.

00:06:18.420 --> 00:06:21.673 position:50% align:center
The sad part is, after that,
I never saw him again.

00:06:21.756 --> 00:06:23.008 position:50% align:center
Oh, dear.

00:06:23.091 --> 00:06:24.968 position:50% align:center
Don't you guys think
we ought to break it to her?

00:06:25.051 --> 00:06:26.970 position:50% align:center
That is the ethical thing to do.

00:06:27.053 --> 00:06:28.179 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Huh?

00:06:28.263 --> 00:06:30.765 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Wanna tell us
why you're blushing?

00:06:30.849 --> 00:06:32.475 position:50% align:center
Earth to Ao Manaka.

00:06:32.559 --> 00:06:35.228 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
What...?!

00:06:35.311 --> 00:06:37.230 position:50% align:center
You're him? Or... her?

00:06:37.313 --> 00:06:39.524 position:50% align:center
The kid from the camping trip?

00:06:39.607 --> 00:06:41.943 position:50% align:center
My name does sound kinda boyish.

00:06:42.027 --> 00:06:44.154 position:50% align:center
And my hair was
really short back then.

00:06:44.237 --> 00:06:45.321 position:50% align:center
So, uh...

00:06:45.405 --> 00:06:47.198 position:50% align:center
Do you remember me
from that night at camp?

00:06:47.282 --> 00:06:48.408 position:50% align:center
Of course I do!

00:06:48.491 --> 00:06:50.118 position:50% align:center
I've been trying to
discover an asteroid

00:06:50.201 --> 00:06:52.620 position:50% align:center
ever since we talked about it!

00:06:52.704 --> 00:06:53.872 position:50% align:center
And look!

00:06:53.955 --> 00:06:55.665 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
A whale charm?

00:06:55.749 --> 00:06:57.042 position:50% align:center
Oh, I see.

00:06:57.125 --> 00:06:59.544 position:50% align:center
You thought that would
help you remember my name.

00:07:00.378 --> 00:07:02.380 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Uh-huh.

00:07:02.464 --> 00:07:03.840 position:50% align:center
Quite the development.

00:07:03.923 --> 00:07:07.510 position:50% align:center
Yeah, things have taken
an interesting turn!

00:07:07.594 --> 00:07:09.262 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
And so, the boy I met that night

00:07:09.346 --> 00:07:12.682 position:50% align:center
at the campsite turned
out to be a girl!

00:08:51.281 --> 00:08:52.657 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Good evening!

00:08:52.741 --> 00:08:55.493 position:50% align:center
Today was a big surprise!

00:08:55.577 --> 00:09:00.415 position:50% align:center
I never imagined you'd be in the
same high school club as me!

00:09:00.498 --> 00:09:02.625 position:50% align:center
I'm so happy we're reunited!

00:09:02.709 --> 00:09:05.253 position:50% align:center
I'm really sorry
I mistook you for a boy.

00:09:05.337 --> 00:09:07.756 position:50% align:center
It's good to see you again!

00:09:07.839 --> 00:09:09.716 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Mom! I need help!

00:09:09.799 --> 00:09:10.925 position:50% align:center
I'm borrowing the book!

00:09:11.009 --> 00:09:12.218 position:50% align:center
[SHIORI]
Huh?

00:09:17.015 --> 00:09:20.226 position:50% align:center
[SHIORI] Is she planning to get
a part-time job or something?

00:09:22.687 --> 00:09:24.314 position:50% align:center
[MIRA groans]

00:09:26.107 --> 00:09:27.609 position:50% align:center
[SUZU]
Mira.

00:09:27.692 --> 00:09:30.028 position:50% align:center
Hey, is something
the matter with you?

00:09:30.111 --> 00:09:31.696 position:50% align:center
C'mon, you've
finally been reunited

00:09:31.780 --> 00:09:34.824 position:50% align:center
with your old flame from
that fateful night so long ago!

00:09:34.908 --> 00:09:36.076 position:50% align:center
Smile!

00:09:36.159 --> 00:09:38.453 position:50% align:center
My old flame? Please.

00:09:38.536 --> 00:09:41.164 position:50% align:center
You're having entirely
too much fun with this.

00:09:41.247 --> 00:09:42.832 position:50% align:center
You're always mean
to anyone who tries

00:09:42.916 --> 00:09:45.126 position:50% align:center
to get close to
me, so what gives?

00:09:45.210 --> 00:09:46.336 position:50% align:center
Duh.

00:09:46.419 --> 00:09:48.171 position:50% align:center
Manaka's a girl, and
a super cute one, too--

00:09:48.254 --> 00:09:50.048 position:50% align:center
it's not the same.

00:09:50.131 --> 00:09:52.884 position:50% align:center
I so support you
getting close to other girls.

00:09:52.967 --> 00:09:54.427 position:50% align:center
[MIRA whimpers]

00:09:54.511 --> 00:09:56.763 position:50% align:center
[SUZU]
So, what's your deal?

00:09:56.846 --> 00:09:58.973 position:50% align:center
Look.

00:09:59.057 --> 00:10:01.434 position:50% align:center
[SUZU]
Hmm, pretty formal.

00:10:01.518 --> 00:10:05.188 position:50% align:center
I remember her being so much
more open and expressive.

00:10:05.271 --> 00:10:06.898 position:50% align:center
Do you think her
tone could mean

00:10:06.981 --> 00:10:09.317 position:50% align:center
that she doesn't
like me anymore?

00:10:09.401 --> 00:10:11.361 position:50% align:center
[SUZU]
I only see one problem here.

00:10:11.444 --> 00:10:12.737 position:50% align:center
Too many texts.

00:10:12.821 --> 00:10:14.739 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
What are you talking about?

00:10:14.823 --> 00:10:15.907 position:50% align:center
[SUZU]
If you're that worried about it,

00:10:15.990 --> 00:10:17.867 position:50% align:center
why don't you go talk
to her in person?

00:10:17.951 --> 00:10:19.369 position:50% align:center
You know what
I've always considered to be

00:10:19.452 --> 00:10:20.578 position:50% align:center
your best quality?

00:10:20.662 --> 00:10:23.289 position:50% align:center
You take action
without overthinking.

00:10:23.373 --> 00:10:25.125 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Mm-hmm!

00:10:25.208 --> 00:10:26.459 position:50% align:center
--Excuse me!
--[STUDENTS gasping]

00:10:26.543 --> 00:10:28.461 position:50% align:center
But then you take it too far!

00:10:28.545 --> 00:10:29.629 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Oh, hi!

00:10:29.713 --> 00:10:32.173 position:50% align:center
Ao! Wanna eat lunch
together today?

00:10:32.257 --> 00:10:33.967 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS]
Huh...?

00:10:34.050 --> 00:10:35.093 position:50% align:center
Sorry about that.

00:10:35.176 --> 00:10:37.178 position:50% align:center
Mira has no chill whatsoever.

00:10:37.262 --> 00:10:38.763 position:50% align:center
It's fine.

00:10:38.847 --> 00:10:42.225 position:50% align:center
Ao, I'm sorry for bombarding you
with all those texts last night!

00:10:42.308 --> 00:10:43.226 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Huh?

00:10:43.309 --> 00:10:44.686 position:50% align:center
I am so embarrassed.

00:10:44.769 --> 00:10:46.771 position:50% align:center
I really wasn't
trying to annoy you.

00:10:46.855 --> 00:10:48.189 position:50% align:center
No-- No way!

00:10:48.273 --> 00:10:50.191 position:50% align:center
Why did you think
that I was annoyed?

