"Aim for an Asteroid"?

00:19:11.443 --> 00:19:12.819 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
Mm-hmm!

00:19:12.902 --> 00:19:14.404 position:50% align:center
Really?

00:19:14.487 --> 00:19:16.823 position:50% align:center
You girls have a lot of nerve,
trying to steal the spotlight.

00:19:16.906 --> 00:19:18.324 position:50% align:center
It's gonna be
a challenge getting you all

00:19:18.408 --> 00:19:20.285 position:50% align:center
to work together.

00:19:20.368 --> 00:19:21.703 position:50% align:center
But it'll be worth the effort.

00:19:21.786 --> 00:19:23.538 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] This is hard.
I'm drawing a blank.

00:19:23.621 --> 00:19:25.623 position:50% align:center
Sorry to interrupt just when
you're getting things going,

00:19:25.707 --> 00:19:27.667 position:50% align:center
but it's time to wrap
it up for the day.

00:19:27.751 --> 00:19:29.586 position:50% align:center
Hey, let's go home, you guys!

00:19:29.669 --> 00:19:31.212 position:50% align:center
What about, "Heaven and Earth"?

00:19:31.296 --> 00:19:32.672 position:50% align:center
No. That isn't it.

00:19:32.756 --> 00:19:33.882 position:50% align:center
And why not?

00:19:33.965 --> 00:19:36.426 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
It needs to be something cuter.

00:19:36.509 --> 00:19:38.094 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Cuter?

00:19:38.178 --> 00:19:39.929 position:50% align:center
They're not even listening.

00:19:40.013 --> 00:19:42.640 position:50% align:center
Who wants to
grab a cheese burger?

00:19:42.724 --> 00:19:43.641 position:50% align:center
[GIRLS]
Hmm?!

00:19:43.725 --> 00:19:45.143 position:50% align:center
[ENDOU whimpers]

00:19:48.229 --> 00:19:51.149 position:50% align:center
Ah! So pretty!

00:19:51.232 --> 00:19:53.068 position:50% align:center
I do think something
that really encompasses

00:19:53.151 --> 00:19:55.487 position:50% align:center
the beauty of rocks
would be ideal.

00:19:55.570 --> 00:19:57.405 position:50% align:center
[INOSE] I hear that,
but why don't we wait

00:19:57.489 --> 00:19:59.282 position:50% align:center
to brainstorm over burgers?

00:19:59.366 --> 00:20:01.826 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Okay. Man, I'm starved.

00:20:05.288 --> 00:20:06.706 position:50% align:center
[GIRLS]
Sparkle?

00:20:06.790 --> 00:20:07.832 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Mm-hmm.

00:20:07.916 --> 00:20:09.334 position:50% align:center
That's a great idea!

00:20:09.417 --> 00:20:12.212 position:50% align:center
Yeah, because both
gems and stars sparkle!

00:20:12.295 --> 00:20:14.547 position:50% align:center
Uh! It's not too weird, is it?

00:20:14.631 --> 00:20:17.050 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Mm-mm. I think it's adorable!

00:20:17.133 --> 00:20:18.927 position:50% align:center
I'm all for a sparkly name!

00:20:19.010 --> 00:20:20.720 position:50% align:center
Sparkly.

00:20:25.266 --> 00:20:27.143 position:50% align:center
Inose? I'm sorry.

00:20:27.227 --> 00:20:29.229 position:50% align:center
I was so focused on
doing my job properly

00:20:29.312 --> 00:20:31.022 position:50% align:center
and playing by the rules.

00:20:31.106 --> 00:20:33.650 position:50% align:center
I guess I lost sight of the fact
that we need more people

00:20:33.733 --> 00:20:35.902 position:50% align:center
to understand what
our club even does.

00:20:35.985 --> 00:20:37.612 position:50% align:center
Vice President...

00:20:37.696 --> 00:20:39.948 position:50% align:center
But now, I see the path clearly.

00:20:40.031 --> 00:20:42.534 position:50% align:center
We should break down the walls
between ourselves first!

00:20:42.617 --> 00:20:43.910 position:50% align:center
Exactly.

00:20:43.993 --> 00:20:45.620 position:50% align:center
So, with that in mind...

00:20:45.704 --> 00:20:47.997 position:50% align:center
What do you think
of this project?

00:20:48.081 --> 00:20:51.001 position:50% align:center
[INOSE] I'm always surprised
by her awkward side.

00:20:53.003 --> 00:20:55.255 position:50% align:center
[ENDOU] Well? How is
everyone getting along?

00:20:55.338 --> 00:20:57.716 position:50% align:center
Honestly, I was worried
about Sakurai and her habit

00:20:57.799 --> 00:21:00.510 position:50% align:center
of being prickly around
people she doesn't know.

00:21:00.593 --> 00:21:02.762 position:50% align:center
[MORINO] Inose's doing
a good job of mediating,

00:21:02.846 --> 00:21:04.681 position:50% align:center
so it's going
pretty well so far.

00:21:04.764 --> 00:21:07.308 position:50% align:center
I see. Well. That's good.

00:21:07.392 --> 00:21:10.603 position:50% align:center
Oh. I'm happy to report
an addition to the budget.

00:21:11.438 --> 00:21:12.772 position:50% align:center
[ENDOU]
Here you go.

00:21:12.856 --> 00:21:13.773 position:50% align:center
[MORINO]
Huh?

00:21:13.857 --> 00:21:15.025 position:50% align:center
It should be fun.

00:21:15.108 --> 00:21:17.736 position:50% align:center
Just make sure everyone's
free next weekend.

00:21:17.819 --> 00:21:20.363 position:50% align:center
[MORINO] So, you want to
do this, no matter what, then?

00:21:22.574 --> 00:21:23.992 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
I love winter.

00:21:24.075 --> 00:21:26.828 position:50% align:center
The constellations
are so pretty right now.

00:21:26.911 --> 00:21:28.038 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Yeah.

00:21:29.456 --> 00:21:30.665 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Hey, Ao?

00:21:30.749 --> 00:21:31.958 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Hmm?

00:21:32.042 --> 00:21:33.251 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] I think it's
so amazing that we're able

00:21:33.335 --> 00:21:36.921 position:50% align:center
to watch the stars and
chat together like this.

00:21:37.005 --> 00:21:38.673 position:50% align:center
I'm glad we're reunited.

00:21:38.757 --> 00:21:41.551 position:50% align:center
It's crazy, don't you think?

00:21:41.634 --> 00:21:43.636 position:50% align:center
Uh, Ao?

00:21:43.720 --> 00:21:45.638 position:50% align:center
[AO]
I'm glad, too.

00:21:45.722 --> 00:21:48.308 position:50% align:center
I always hoped
that I'd see you again.

00:21:48.391 --> 00:21:51.061 position:50% align:center
And now it's finally happened.

00:21:51.144 --> 00:21:52.645 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Mm.

00:21:53.813 --> 00:21:55.648 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Well, I'd better go.

00:21:55.732 --> 00:21:56.900 position:50% align:center
See you at school!

00:21:56.983 --> 00:21:58.193 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Okay.

00:22:02.030 --> 00:22:04.532 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
I want to find one.

00:22:04.616 --> 00:22:07.160 position:50% align:center
[AO]
We'll make it happen.

00:22:07.243 --> 00:22:11.331 position:50% align:center
[AO, MIRA] Just like we said,
when we made our promise.

00:23:46.009 --> 00:23:49.220 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] Next time:
"The Riverside Milky Way."